##You had to drink pot medicine to get in? Is this a precaution or a distraction?

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

This kind of formalism, regardless of science, may not only harm the health of students, but also add chaos to the prevention and control of the epidemic.

By Shen Lin

The combination of traditional Chinese medicine and Western medicine has been emphasized in the series of new coronary pneumonia treatment plans issued by the National Health Commission. Clinical evidence shows that TCM prescription has unique advantages in reducing fever and cough symptoms, controlling disease progression, and enhancing human immunity.

However, the announcement by the Yunnan Lincang Sports and Education Bureau that all primary and secondary schools in Lincang were forced to take "big pot medicine" has triggered strong dissatisfaction among some students' parents in Lincang city of Yunnan Province

On February 28, the Lincang government held a special preparatory work meeting for the city-wide resumption of education and epidemic prevention and control. At the meeting, Mayor Zhang Zhizheng, deputy secretary of the Municipal Party Committee, stressed the need to earnestly implement the requirements of precise prevention and control and precise implementation of policies, take active and effective prevention and control measures, do a good job in the spring semester 2020 preparations, to prevent the outbreak of the epidemic in the campus, to ensure the safety of teachers and students and physical health.

On February 29, the Lincang Linxiang District Education and Sports Bureau, Lincang No. 2 Middle School and other institutions and schools issued notices requiring teachers, students and parents to drink "big pot medicine" to strengthen the body's resistance, to prepare for the resumption of education and classes affected by the new coronavirus epidemic.

"since March 1, Parents have been required to upload photos of drinking drugs to class groups every day before 5 pm, " said a group chat transcript provided by a parent who claimed to be from Linxiang District, Lincang, after the announcement was posted.

In the notice, the kindergarten in addition to requiring students to upload daily pictures of drinking medicine, but also need to write "drink drugs after there is no abnormal, such as diarrhea, dizziness, " and even lead to parents' panic and anger.

In response, some legal experts said that the compulsory administration of drugs may violate the Drug Administration Law, the basic medical care and health promotion law, and other risks. If the circumstances are serious, it may violate the criminal law. "In the event of a mass adverse event due to the above-mentioned circumstances, the decision-makers and implementers of the regulation will be held responsible for possible charges including abuse of power, illegal medical practice, etc. . "

On March 2, after the announcement was made, Lincang, Yunnan Province, urgently corrected the wrong practice of forcing teachers and students to take "big pot medicine" and issued a "circular on teachers and students taking "Big Pot medicine" in Lincang schools. Lincang Education and Sports Bureau, said the drug taking is based on voluntary principle; the controversial practice, the Individual Education and Sports Bureau, municipal schools launched, currently "not to implement the original notice" , the opening time has been postponed. "I am deeply sorry for the inconvenience caused to the parents and teachers and the adverse impact on the society. "

In addition, Lincang Education and Sports Bureau also said that the pot medicine can not prevent new pneumonia, introduced to improve the immunity of teachers and students.

Local people in Lincang say that at the end of each season, students are often organized to drink "pot medicine" , "has become a habit and tradition. ". In addition to Lincang, many medical institutions in Yunnan have given free "big pot medicine" to frontline staff in the fight against the epidemic. "Big Pot medicine" has a long history in Yunnan and other places, and some local residents have also used it to prevent diseases and strengthen the body's immunity.

"Big Pot medicine" , generally refers to the traditional ethnic folk medicine that is boiled in a big pot. Zhai Huaqiang, a professor at the Beijing University of Chinese Medicine of traditional Chinese medicine, told the media that officials in the Tang and song dynasties had a tradition of distributing fixed ready-to-use medicines to people to fight the plague, "As far as the published adult formulas are concerned, the properties of the 17 kinds of medicines are relatively mild and the dosage is relatively small. Most of the medicines belong to the dual-use of food and medicine. Taking them is relatively safe and has certain curative effects. " Therefore, he believes that special period boil "big pot medicine" should not be opposed, but also need to pay attention not to "partial generalization" and enforcement.

News Map

Doctors of the Acupuncture Service aerators of the Shanghai First People's Hospital also told the Xinmin Weekly that although the prescription of "big pot medicine" is not a big problem, it still depends on the individual's physical condition, but it is by no means a one-size-fits-all requirement: "The news says that there is a tradition here, and we don't comment on things that are in good public order; but the school treats eating big pots of medicine as a condition of admission, and the people are disgusted by the enforcement. And this time, the big pot of medicine is for parents to go to the pharmacy to buy, which has added an economic burden to the masses."

At a State Council news conference on February 29, Wang Rongbing, director of the Department of Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western medicine at Temple of Earth Hospital in Beijing, also stressed that some of the drugs previously recommended were for the treatment of symptoms and not for prevention, "there is no point in not advocating the use of proprietary Chinese medicine for people without symptoms. ".

Moreover, Lincang City in Yunnan is far from the need for everyone to drink medicine to prevent the degree of new crown pneumonia. As of February 28, a cumulative total of one confirmed case has been reported in Lincang, which has been cured and discharged from hospital for more than two weeks, and there are no suspected cases. Apart from possible import-type risks, the risk of proliferation within Lincang is not high enough to require everyone to drink Chinese medicine.

As the Guangming Daily pointed out: The local education bureau or school, in making any decision, we need to consider the health of students first, rather than under the pretext of epidemic prevention to make some arbitrary decision. This kind of formalism, regardless of science, may not only harm the health of students, but also add chaos to the prevention and control of the epidemic.
